SUMMARY:[Hike - Intermediate] 10Km Fast Pace - Heber Down - Whitby
DESCRIPTION:GTA Hiking & Stuff\nHeber Down Conservation!\n\nThis is a **fa
 st-paced** intermediate hike (**Going between 4.5-5km/hr**) with few stops
 . The beginning will be flat with the paved sections\, and we will be goin
 g into the back trails\, where there will be mud/snow. We will cover about
  10km in 2 hours\, **with minimal breaks**.\n\n**Not a beginner hike!**\n\
 n**THIS HIKE STARTS AT 9:30AM**\n\nBring a water bottle and dress for the 
 weather.\n\nParts of the trail can get muddy/snowy from the snow. Be prepa
 red.\n\nWe are going to meet at the Old Cullen Gardens parking lot.\nInter
 section Cochrane & Taunton.\n\nGo to the back of the parking lot near the 
 new Pickleball courts. The path starts to the left of the picnic shelter.\
 n\n**Hike leaves promptly at 9:35AM**\n\n**Winter Hiking Season Informatio
 n:**\n\nPlease note that as we get into winter hiking with snow and slippe
 ry trails\, we consider proper Crampons to be mandatory.\nThe event host c
 an ask you not to participate if you don't have proper footwear including 
 Crampons. More [Crampon Information](https://www.meetup.com/gta-hiking-mee
 tup/events/297067178/).\n\n**LEGAL DISCLAIMER AND LIABILITY INFORMATION:**
 \n\nBy RSVP'ing and paying the event fee (if applicable)\, you are confirm
 ing that you have read\, understand and accept the following:\n\n1. **GTA 
 Hiking Meetup is a private group**. Attending events is voluntary by you a
 s a member. Participation in any activity with us is at your own risk.\n2.
  By joining this event as a member you agree to indemnify and hold harmles
 s its organizers\, co-organizers\, assistant organizers\, event hosts\, an
 d other members from all claims or liability of every type (including cour
 t costs and legal fees) for injury or death to any person or for damage to
  property\, loss of personal property or any other wrongful act arising ou
 t of or relating to your participation as a member. This agreement applies
  to you and to other persons (as your guests) who may accompany you in the
 se endeavors.\n3. You also agree to hold the organizers as well as other g
 roup members harmless. By participating voluntarily in the group\, you exp
 ressly waive any and all such claims against each and every other member i
 n the group\, including without limitation any and all claims against the 
 group organizer\, co-organizers\, assistant organizers\, and event hosts.
